The paper deals with data structures and algorithms for maintaining and manipulating lists, which falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS). The use of link-cut trees and their applications to sorting permutations suggest that the paper may also belong to the categories of discrete mathematics (cs.DM), computational geometry (cs.CG), and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). Finally, the use of amortized or worst-case time analysis suggests that the paper may also belong to the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
